# Visible Effect (`src/visible.py`)

Beat-synced objects zoom OUT from the screen center (vanishing point) along fixed axes, then **pop + fade on strong beats**. Built on `lightle.py`'s GPU blur + audio pipeline.

## Lifecycle of an object
1. Spawn at screen center, tiny scale.
2. Zoom in (grow) + fly outward along an axis of `--axes`.
3. On strong beat → **object closest to camera POPs**: burst scale + alpha fade.
4. Auto-die when it leaves the frame OR pop completes.
5. Frame-budget measured in `--lifespan` frames (default tuned around DEFAULT_LIFESPAN ≈ 0.x seconds at 30 FPS).

## Axes presets (`--axes`)
- `horizontal` (default) — 2 dirs: left + right on a **single horizontal axis** (user-requested "2 trục cố định").
- `vertical` — 2 dirs: up + down.
- `diagonal` — 4 corners.
- `cross` — 4 perpendicular.
- `star` — 8 dirs.
Add small randomness with `--angle_jitter` (radians); default 0 = strictly on axis.

## Rendering
- Circles OR `--image_path` (PNG/JPG, alpha used if RGBA).
- Optional per-object glow halo (`--glow 0|1`, default 1).
- Depth = distance from center → scale + brightness. Nearest object to camera (largest scale) is the pop candidate on beats.

## Audio reactivity
- Onset strength drives pop triggers.
- Continuous beat cadence drives spawn rate so objects keep flowing between beats.

## CLI
`--image_path`, `--glow 0|1`, `--lifespan <frames>`, `--axes {horizontal,vertical,diagonal,cross,star}`, `--angle_jitter <rad>`, plus shared flags.

## Do NOT
- Spawn objects off-center — they MUST originate from the vanishing point for the "coming from behind" feel.
- Add per-beat fixed-position spawns (that's rhythm.py); `visible` is continuous flow with beat-triggered pops.
- Hardcode more than the listed axes presets — extend `choices=` in argparse instead.
